# Push to ACR
docker push myacr.azurecr.io/myapp:v1



1. Check Docker Installed
docker --version
What it does

Checks whether Docker is installed and working.

2. Build Docker Image
docker build -t myapp:v1 .
What it does

Builds a Docker image from your Dockerfile.

Breakdown
build → create image
-t → tag/name the image
myapp → image name
v1 → version/tag
. → current folder contains Dockerfile
Example
docker build -t node-api:v1 .
3. Check Built Images
docker images
What it does

Lists all Docker images in your system.

4. Run Container
docker run -d -p 3000:3000 --name mycontainer myapp:v1
What it does

Runs your image as a container.

Breakdown
run → start container
-d → detached/background mode
-p 3000:3000
first 3000 → local machine port
second 3000 → container port
--name → custom container name
myapp:v1 → image name
5. Check Running Containers
docker ps
What it does

Shows running containers.

6. Check All Containers
docker ps -a
What it does

Shows running + stopped containers.

7. View Container Logs
docker logs mycontainer
What it does

Displays application logs inside container.

Live Logs
docker logs -f mycontainer
8. Enter Inside Container
docker exec -it mycontainer bash
What it does

Opens terminal inside running container.

If bash not available
docker exec -it mycontainer sh
9. Stop Container
docker stop mycontainer
What it does

Stops running container.

10. Start Existing Container
docker start mycontainer
What it does

Starts stopped container.

11. Restart Container
docker restart mycontainer
What it does

Restarts container.

12. Remove Container
docker rm mycontainer
What it does

Deletes container.

Force Remove
docker rm -f mycontainer
13. Remove Image
docker rmi myapp:v1
What it does

Deletes Docker image.

14. Test Application

Open browser:

http://localhost:3000

Or use curl:

curl http://localhost:3000
15. Docker Login
Docker Hub Login
docker login
What it does

Authenticates with Docker Hub.

16. Tag Image for Docker Hub
docker tag myapp:v1 username/myapp:v1
Example
docker tag myapp:v1 madhan1417/myapp:v1
What it does

Prepares image for Docker Hub push.

17. Push to Docker Hub
docker push username/myapp:v1
Example
docker push madhan1417/myapp:v1
What it does

Uploads image to Docker Hub.

18. Pull Image Anywhere
docker pull username/myapp:v1
What it does

Downloads image from Docker Hub.

19. Azure ACR Login

Login Azure:

az login

Login ACR:

az acr login --name myacrname
What it does

Authenticates Docker with Azure Container Registry.

20. Tag Image for ACR
docker tag myapp:v1 myacrname.azurecr.io/myapp:v1
Example
docker tag myapp:v1 madhanacr.azurecr.io/myapp:v1
21. Push to Azure ACR
docker push myacrname.azurecr.io/myapp:v1
What it does

Uploads image to Azure Container Registry.

22. Verify Images in ACR
az acr repository list --name myacrname --output table
23. Pull from ACR
docker pull myacrname.azurecr.io/myapp:v1
24. Useful Cleanup Commands
Remove all stopped containers
docker container prune
Remove unused images
docker image prune
Remove everything unused
docker system prune -a

⚠️ Be careful — deletes unused containers/images/networks.



Check Docker Networks : 

docker network ls


Check Docker Volumesb : 

docker volume ls
